Springbok captain Siya Kolisi's star just keeps rising.  Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Springbok captain Siya Kolisi's star just keeps rising. The 2019 world cup skipper has now been named the most influential figure in rugby. READ: Erasmus insisted World Cup trophy glory belong to Kolisi Respected publication Rugby World has Kolisi at the top of the 50 most influential personalities in the game. Kolisi signed with US-based Roc Nation to look after his brand, following last year's victory in Japan.